Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs) are prepared by the high-temperature plasma spraying technique in this paper.
Titulo: Production of Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using Thermal Plasma Spraying Technique

Sentencas: The positive electrolyte and negative functional layers are deposited onto porous alloy substrate using thermal plasma in the air.
Titulo: Production of Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using Thermal Plasma Spraying Technique

Sentencas: The porous alloy supporting component is produced by molding (6x6 cm(2)), pressing (35 ton), and sintering (e.g., 1000 degrees C, 1100 degrees C, 1200 degrees C, and 1250 degrees C).
Titulo: Production of Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using Thermal Plasma Spraying Technique

Sentencas: The 5 x 5-cm(2) MS-SOFC with an effective electrode area of 16 cm(2) shows that the open-circuit voltages are 0.95 V (Cell-1100), 1.09 V (cell-1200), and 1.08 V (Cell-1250) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Production of Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using Thermal Plasma Spraying Technique

Sentencas: In addition, the maximum power at a cell potential of 0.6 V is 5.7 W (Cell-1100), 11.5 W (Cell-1200), and 12.1 W (Cell-1250) at 650 degrees C. Thermal expansion coefficient of porous alloy supporting component is also measured in this paper.
Titulo: Production of Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using Thermal Plasma Spraying Technique

Sentencas: MS-SOFCs without cracking and deforming following thermal plasma spraying process have good electrical performance.
Titulo: Production of Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using Thermal Plasma Spraying Technique

Sentencas: Atmospheric plasma spraying method is revealed as a suitable deposition technique for manufacturing MS-SOFCs.
Titulo: Production of Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Using Thermal Plasma Spraying Technique
